CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 25, 1957, pg. A17 reads: "Escorts...for the 1957 debutantes included, seated, Charles Hampton, Donald Jones, Joseph W. Lee, Earl Harris, Vernon Reynolds, Obadiah Simms, Kermit Matthews. Standing are Roy Bennett, James Fletcher, Donald Moss, Walter Smith, Garfield Ralph, Bloise Avery, William Hampton, Kenneth Holiday, Farris Harris and Robert Sabbath. - All Photos by Harris."image of Farris Harris not in negative, pasted in image published by Pittsburgh Courier.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight young men wearing tuxedos, including possibly, from left, seated: Vernon Reynolds, Obadiah Simms, and Kermit Matthews; standing: Garfield Ralph, Bloise Avery, William Hampton, Kenneth Holiday, and Robert Sabbath, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for the Alpha Kappa Alpha 1957 Cotillion
